&lt;Noranda Inc> has agreed to cut acidrain emissions by 50 pct at its Quebec copper smelter by 1990with the federal and Quebec governments each providing 41.6 mlndlrs towards the cost, the federal industry department said.    Under an agreement, Noranda will also be required to 41.6 mln Canadian dlrs and cover operating costs of theproposed 125 mln dlr sulphuric acid plant.    The department said the agreement will allow Noranda tomeet polutions standards in Quebec's new environmentalregulations passed in 1985. Reuter&#3;